What is true of participles is also true of adjectives. striking instances are Odes 3. 23. 16 fragilique myrto (sprigs of myrtle) ; 4. 5. 23 laudantur simili prole (for likeness in offspring); C. S. 30 spicea donet Cererem corona (with wheat ears for crown). Compare Livy 9. 2. 9 per cavam rupem (through the cleft in the rock).
